title: Why don't more Tatooine-like exoplanets exist in our Milky Way galaxy? Astronomers might have an answer
description: Astronomers may finally understand why planets orbiting two suns, the real-world equivalents of the "Star Wars" planet Tatooine, are so scarce in our galaxy — and it has to do with general relativity.
